<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900518-0087</DOCNO><DOCID>900518-0087.</DOCID><HL>   Marketing Brief -- Pathe Communications Corp.:   Third Payment Is Made   In MGM/UA Acquisition</HL><DATE>05/18/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A3</SO><CO>   PCC MGM</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)</IN><LP>   MGM/UA Communications Co. said Pathe Communications Corp.made the third of four $50 million security deposits towardits $1.27 billion acquisition of MGM/UA.   Culver City, Calif.-based MGM/UA had granted Pathe anextra week, until yesterday, to make the payment. In additionto the $200 million in security deposits, Pathe has grantedMGM/UA a security interest of $75 million in three Pathefilms.</LP><TEXT>   Pathe, a Los Angeles-based entertainment concerncontrolled by Italian financier Giancarlo Parretti, launchedits $20-a-share offer for MGM/UA on March 14. It is set toexpire June 7.</TEXT></DOC>